    "We can see that MTLoRA scales well with a larger backbone, providing significant improvement compared to the single-task models while training significantly fewer parameters.",
    "More analyses are included in the Appendix.",
    "ConclusionIn conclusion, this work introduced MTLoRA, an innovative framework designed to enable parameter-efficient training for Multi-Task Learning (MTL) models.",
    "Central to MTLoRA are the Task-Agnostic and Task-Specific Low-Rank Adaptation modules, which are instrumental in effectively disentangling the parameter space during MTL fine-tuning.",
    "Those modules allow the fine-tuning to balance both task specialization and interaction within MTL environments."
